<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14 is: The Standard Library function memcmp shall not be used to compare null terminated strings.

</misra_rule>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- is_rule_violated: whether the rule is violated or not (true/false),
- scenario: a specific violation scenario.
</response format>
<target_code>
Here is the code of MHD_get_timeout_i:
```c
_MHD_EXTERN int
MHD_get_timeout_i (struct MHD_Daemon *daemon)
{
#if SIZEOF_INT >= SIZEOF_INT64_T
  return MHD_get_timeout64s (daemon);
#else  /* SIZEOF_INT < SIZEOF_INT64_T */
  const int64_t to64 = MHD_get_timeout64s (daemon);
  if (INT_MAX >= to64)
    return (int) to64;
  return INT_MAX;
#endif /* SIZEOF_INT < SIZEOF_INT64_T */
}
```
</target_code>
<target_code>
Here is the code fragment that you need to analyze:
```c
return MHD_get_timeout64s (daemon);
```
Focus on the above code fragment and judge whether it violates the rule 21.14 or not.
</target_code>
scenario: The fragment simply returns the result of MHD_get_timeout64s(daemon). There is no use of memcmp or any string comparison (null-terminated or otherwise), so MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.14 is not violated.
